values:
Hello.

I'm halfway through the Dune miniseries. It's very good so far.

I'm sorry to have to inform everyone, but music officially sucks now. It's been pretty shitty for a while, but i'll go ahead and announce it: Music Sucks Now. There are just too many walking cliches around now. Too many bands that should have stopped before they started.

I've been having more seizures. These tend to lead to some pretty righteous dreams. Maybe they are clues to some greater mystery. It hurts like a bitch to come out of them, though.

Heroes finally came back, but I haven't watched the newest one yet. I'll do that after I finish Dune. 

People keep telling me to watch Lost, which I would like to do, but i'm already caught up in Heroes, the Sopranos, and the Riches
so I don't need to add more to my plate.

Later.

R.
Anna Nicole Smith died of a drug overdose. Big fucking surprise. Now maybe the news will cover something interesting and actually prescient to the times.

Malcom McDowell is on Heroes. My life is officially a little better.
I'm ready for it to not be cold anymore.
Fuck you cold.
You suck.
R.

So. Black Snake Moan is pretty much the best fucking movie ever. It was even better than Hustle and Flow, which is a hard act to follow.
Wild Hogs hopefully tonight.
Purple Rain Movie Night on Tuesday.
Bad Dudes on the 16th.
Dad bought a new dog. That brings the count up to 4.
The Films of Kenneth Anger Vol.1 is out. I'm excited.
Jim Goad's Big Book of Sex will be out in about a month. Again, very excited.
I'm going to go eat now.
R.

Damned sinuses. Always giving me trouble.  
Wild Hogs comes out today. I'm very psyched.
Martin Season 2 comes out in May. Again, very psyched.
It's really nice out. I think i'll walk around the woods a bit.
R.

Well. I'm back. I should be updating this regularly. I would say more, but I must take care of my sick brother (he caught a rather wicked sinus infection.) Write me back.
R.
